  "source_id": "diverticulitis",
  "name": "Diverticulitis - Antibiotic Regimen Query (Cipro + Metro)",
  "description": "Tests ability to find diverticulitis patients via the standard antibiotic regimen — ciprofloxacin + metronidazole. High cross-indication: cipro is also for UTI/respiratory; metronidazole for C. diff/anaerobic infections. The combination is more specific to intra-abdominal infections than either alone.",
  "prompt": "Find patients prescribed both ciprofloxacin and metronidazole — the standard outpatient antibiotic regimen for diverticulitis.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find patients on cipro and metronidazole.",
    "broad": "Find patients prescribed ciprofloxacin or metronidazole — the standard outpatient antibiotic regimen for uncomplicated diverticulitis (also used for other intra-abdominal infections).",
    "expert": "I need to identify patients treated pharmacologically for diverticulitis via the standard antibiotic regimen. Search MedicationRequest resources for ciprofloxacin and metronidazole, each coded in RxNorm; the combination is characteristic of intra-abdominal infection management and is more specific to diverticulitis than either drug alone. This medication-only cohort will have meaningful cross-indication overlap — ciprofloxacin is commonly used for urinary tract infections and metronidazole for anaerobic infections including C. difficile — so the captured population will include patients treated for conditions other than diverticulitis."
  },
